On Thu, Feb 14, 2002 at 03:59:31PM -0700, Alejandro Vieira wrote:
> I have a quick question before I do. Should the oil drain plug on
> a T4 motor have a washer (1977, original motor)? I noticed when

IIRC it does. I think it's copper?

> another question: what's that plate at the bottom of the oil
> filler tube for? Looks like it's held on by 2 10mm bolts?

That's the oil sump plate. It's where you might install a oil temp
sensor if so inclined (such as me). FYI the sealing element of this
plate is an o-ring that on mine seems to make a very nice seal.


